{"at":805829517.996944,"outcome":{"note":{}},"detail":"thinking: ---\n\n## Investigation Report — Issue #25: Guard Score() and scoreFromMetrics\n\n### 1. Project context\n\n- **Module**: `github.com\/iksnae\/code-certification` (Go 1.25.5)\n- **Target file**: `internal\/engine\/scorer.go` (and its test `scorer_test.go`)\n- **Key dependencies**: `internal\/domain`, `internal\/policy`, `internal\/analysis`, `internal\/evidence`, `internal\/report`\n\n### 2. `language_tiers` package — does NOT exist\n\nThere is **no** `internal\/language_tiers\/` directory or any file defining `TierForLanguage`, `TierGeneric`, or `TierNone`. This package must be **created from scratch**. The closest existing concept is in `internal\/doctor\/doctor.go` lines 641–667, which has a different \"Tier 1\/Tier 2\" taxonomy (tree-sitter vs LSP) — not relevant here.\n\nFour languages have registered analyzers (via `init()` in the `analysis` package):\n\n| File | Registration |\n|---|---|\n| `internal\/analysis\/go_analyzer.go:20` | `Register(\"go\", ...)` |\n| `internal\/analysis\/ts_analyzer.go:23` | `Register(\"ts\", ...)` and `Register(\"js\", ...)` |\n| `internal\/analysis\/python_analyzer.go:23` | `Register(\"py\", ...)` |\n| `internal\/analysis\/rust_analyzer.go:23` | `Register(\"rs\", ...)` |\n\nAll other languages mapped in `internal\/discovery\/generic.go`'s `certifiableExts` (swift, java, ruby, c, cpp, php, elixir, scala, lua, r, zig, sql, proto, etc.) have **no parser capability** — they are \"TierGeneric\" by the issue's definition.\n\n`analysis.ForLanguage(lang)` returns `nil` for all of them.\n\n### 3. `Score()` function — current state\n\n**File**: `internal\/engine\/scorer.go:13–67`  \n**Current signature**:\n\n```go\nfunc Score(ev []domain.Evidence, evalResult policy.EvaluationResult) domain.DimensionScores\n```\n\n- Does **NOT** receive any language or unit info\n- Cannot distinguish TierGeneric from TierCapable\n- The doc comment claims _\"Only dimensions with actual evidence are included ... unmeasured dimensions are absent\"_\n\n**Callers** (must all be updated when signature changes):\n\n| File | Line | Context |\n|---|---|---|\n| `internal\/engine\/pipeline.go` | 25 | `scores := Score(ev, evalResult)` — has `unit domain.Unit` in scope |\n| `internal\/engine\/scorer_test.go` | ~25+ call sites | Each passing `ev, evalResult` — must add a language string |\n\n### 4. The `complexity <= 5 → maintainability 0.95` trap\n\n**File**: `internal\/engine\/scorer.go:93–108` (`scoreFromMetrics`)\n\n```go\ncomplexity := metricOrSummaryInt(e, \"complexity\", \"complexity\")\nif complexity >= 0 {   \/\/ ← complexity=0 passes this check\n    switch {\n    case complexity <= 5:\n        setMax(scores, domain.DimMaintainability, 0.95)  \/\/ ← FIRES on unmeasured 0\n```\n\n`evidence.CodeMetrics.ToEvidence()` always includes `\"complexity\": float64(m.Complexity)`. For non-Go files, `ComputeMetrics(src)` sets `Complexity: 0` (the zero value of the struct field). The cyclomatic complexity computation only runs for Go via `ComputeGoComplexity`. So every Swift, Ruby, Java, etc. file gets `complexity=0` → maintainability=0.95.\n\n### 5. The 0.5 defaults — violation injection\n\n**File**: `internal\/engine\/scorer.go:59–66`\n\n```go\nfor _, v := range evalResult.Violations {\n    penalty := severityPenalty(v.Severity)\n    if _, ok := scores[v.Dimension]; ok {\n        scores[v.Dimension] = max(0, scores[v.Dimension]-penalty)\n    } else {\n        \/\/ Violation introduces the dimension at a penalized value\n        scores[v.Dimension] = max(0, 0.80-penalty)  \/\/ ← INJECTS 0.50 for SeverityError\n    }\n}\n```\n\nFor a \"missing evidence\" violation with `SeverityError` (penalty=0.30): introduces dimension at **0.50**. This is how Swift units get `correctness=0.5` and `testability=0.5` — the policy template's `lint-clean` and `test-pass` rules produce missing-evidence violations for these dimensions.\n\nThis `else` branch directly contradicts the doc contract.\n\n### 6. Domain types that need additions\n\n**`domain.Grade`** (`internal\/domain\/dimension.go:89–107`): No `GradeNA` constant. Currently has GradeA through GradeF.\n\n**`domain.CertificationRecord`** (`internal\/domain\/record.go:69–98`): No `Unsupported bool` field.\n\n**`gradeEmoji`** (`internal\/report\/card.go:266–278`): Already has a `default: return \"⚪\"` fallback, which works for N\/A.\n\n### 7. Report aggregation — currently unaware of Unsupported\n\n- **`report.GenerateCard`** (`internal\/report\/card.go:54–97`): Iterates all records, uses `r.Score` and `r.Grade.String()` without checking for `Unsupported`. An N\/A grade would stringify as `\"N\/A\"` (once `GradeNA` is added) and `domain.GradeFromScore(0)` would return `GradeF`, which is wrong.\n- **`report.buildLanguageDetail`** (`internal\/report\/full.go:149–189`): Same issue — includes all units in language aggregates.\n- **`report.computeDimensionAverages`** (in `full.go`): Also needs to skip.\n\n### 8. Summary of required changes (scope)\n\n| # | What | Where |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | **Create** `internal\/language_tiers\/` package with `Tier` type, `TierCapable`\/`TierGeneric`\/`TierNone`, `TierForLanguage()` | New directory |\n| 2 | **Add** `GradeNA` constant and `\"N\/A\"` string mapping | `internal\/domain\/dimension.go` |\n| 3 | **Add** `Unsupported bool` field | `internal\/domain\/record.go` (`CertificationRecord`) |\n| 4 | **Change** `Score()` signature to accept `language string`; add pre-scoring gate for TierGeneric → short-circuit return | `internal\/engine\/scorer.go` |\n| 5 | **Guard** `scoreFromMetrics` complexity rule with tier check | `internal\/engine\/scorer.go` |\n| 6 | **Remove** violation `else` injection branch | `internal\/engine\/scorer.go` |\n| 7 | **Update** `CertifyUnit` to handle Unsupported short-circuit (set Grade=N\/A, Score=0, skip normal flow) | `internal\/engine\/pipeline.go` |\n| 8 | **Filter** Unsupported units from aggregates | `internal\/report\/card.go`, `internal\/report\/full.go` |\n| 9 | **Update** all test callers with new `Score` signature | `internal\/engine\/scorer_test.go`, `internal\/engine\/pipeline_test.go`, `internal\/integration_test.go` |\n| 10 | **Run** `go test .\/... -count=1` | Verify |\n\n### 9. Decisions recorded\n\nAll key architectural decisions (package structure, signature changes, domain additions, violation handling strategy) have been recorded to the journal at `.agencyx\/journal\/25.md`.","ticketId":"25","id":"25-854","phase":"planning"}
